randoop.types

Class GenericType

  • java.lang.Object
    • randoop.types.GeneralType
      • randoop.types.GenericType
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GenericArrayType, GenericClassType

    public abstract class GenericType
extends GeneralType
    Represents generic types that can occur as class declarations, formal parameters or return types.

    In Randoop, meant to be instantiated to a ConcreteType rather than be used directly in tests.

    See Also:
    GenericClassType, GenericArrayType, GenericSimpleType

      • forType

        public static GenericType forType(java.lang.reflect.Type type)
                           throws RandoopTypeException
        Builds a generic type from the object reference by the given Type reference. The type must either represent a generic array, or a generic class.
        Parameters:
        type - the object from which the generic type is to be built
        Returns:
        a GenericType object constructed from the given type
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the type is neither a generic array or class
